[{"id":"VR837548","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram. The diagram extends from a synapse to a cell membrane. Dendrites extend outward from the cell membrane. The cell membrane connects to an axon, which is covered by the myelin sheath. The myelin sheath consists of several parts. The synapse follows the end of the axon.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR837548.g03.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The figure shows the myelin sheath, a semipermeable membrane that provides support and helps speed up the action potential in neurons. What condition occurs when the immune system causes the deterioration of the myelin sheath?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR837548_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Alzheimerâ€™s disease</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Multiple sclerosis</p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Autism</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Myasthenia gravis</p>"],"answer":1}]